{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":904,"text":"I used to think"},{"time":2207,"text":"the whole purpose of life\nwas pursuing happiness."},{"time":6680,"text":"Everyone said the path\nto happiness was success,"},{"time":10088,"text":"so I searched for that ideal job,"},{"time":12610,"text":"that perfect boyfriend,\nthat beautiful apartment."},{"time":16998,"text":"But instead of ever feeling fulfilled,"},{"time":20020,"text":"I felt anxious and adrift."},{"time":23195,"text":"And I wasn't alone; my friends --\nthey struggled with this, too."}]},{"cues":[{"time":28720,"text":"Eventually, I decided to go\nto graduate school for positive psychology"},{"time":33013,"text":"to learn what truly makes people happy."},{"time":36971,"text":"But what I discovered there\nchanged my life."},{"time":40452,"text":"The data showed that chasing happiness\ncan make people unhappy."},{"time":45967,"text":"And what really struck me was this:"},{"time":49058,"text":"the suicide rate has been rising\naround the world,"},{"time":51869,"text":"and it recently reached\na 30-year high in America."},{"time":55753,"text":"Even though life is getting\nobjectively better"},{"time":58540,"text":"by nearly every conceivable standard,"},{"time":61254,"text":"more people feel hopeless,"},{"time":63477,"text":"depressed and alone."},{"time":66214,"text":"There's an emptiness\ngnawing away at people,"},{"time":69051,"text":"and you don't have to be\nclinically depressed to feel it."},{"time":72345,"text":"Sooner or later, I think we all wonder:"},{"time":75784,"text":"Is this all there is?"},{"time":79167,"text":"And according to the research,\nwhat predicts this despair"},{"time":82397,"text":"is not a lack of happiness."},{"time":84248,"text":"It's a lack of something else,"},{"time":86817,"text":"a lack of having meaning in life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":90962,"text":"But that raised some questions for me."},{"time":93855,"text":"Is there more to life than being happy?"},{"time":97216,"text":"And what's the difference\nbetween being happy"},{"time":99663,"text":"and having meaning in life?"},{"time":102879,"text":"Many psychologists define happiness\nas a state of comfort and ease,"},{"time":107503,"text":"feeling good in the moment."},{"time":110098,"text":"Meaning, though, is deeper."},{"time":112278,"text":"The renowned psychologist\nMartin Seligman says"},{"time":114866,"text":"meaning comes from belonging to\nand serving something beyond yourself"},{"time":119537,"text":"and from developing the best within you."},{"time":123617,"text":"Our culture is obsessed with happiness,"},{"time":126236,"text":"but I came to see that seeking meaning\nis the more fulfilling path."},{"time":130367,"text":"And the studies show that people\nwho have meaning in life,"},{"time":133320,"text":"they're more resilient,"},{"time":134754,"text":"they do better in school and at work,"},{"time":137335,"text":"and they even live longer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":139985,"text":"So this all made me wonder:"},{"time":142030,"text":"How can we each live more meaningfully?"},{"time":145980,"text":"To find out, I spent five years\ninterviewing hundreds of people"},{"time":149682,"text":"and reading through thousands\nof pages of psychology,"},{"time":152607,"text":"neuroscience and philosophy."},{"time":155366,"text":"Bringing it all together,"},{"time":157179,"text":"I found that there are what I call\nfour pillars of a meaningful life."},{"time":162544,"text":"And we can each create lives of meaning"},{"time":165002,"text":"by building some or all\nof these pillars in our lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":169428,"text":"The first pillar is belonging."},{"time":172378,"text":"Belonging comes\nfrom being in relationships"},{"time":174709,"text":"where you're valued\nfor who you are intrinsically"},{"time":177438,"text":"and where you value others as well."},{"time":180218,"text":"But some groups and relationships\ndeliver a cheap form of belonging;"},{"time":184932,"text":"you're valued for what you believe,"},{"time":186849,"text":"for who you hate,"},{"time":188119,"text":"not for who you are."},{"time":190420,"text":"True belonging springs from love."},{"time":193227,"text":"It lives in moments among individuals,"},{"time":196236,"text":"and it's a choice -- you can choose\nto cultivate belonging with others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200661,"text":"Here's an example."},{"time":202292,"text":"Each morning, my friend Jonathan\nbuys a newspaper"},{"time":205871,"text":"from the same street vendor in New York."},{"time":208502,"text":"They don't just conduct\na transaction, though."},{"time":210806,"text":"They take a moment to slow down, talk,"},{"time":213513,"text":"and treat each other like humans."},{"time":216038,"text":"But one time, Jonathan\ndidn't have the right change,"},{"time":219456,"text":"and the vendor said,"},{"time":220700,"text":"\"Don't worry about it.\""},{"time":222244,"text":"But Jonathan insisted on paying,"},{"time":224755,"text":"so he went to the store\nand bought something he didn't need"},{"time":227791,"text":"to make change."},{"time":229992,"text":"But when he gave the money to the vendor,"},{"time":232639,"text":"the vendor drew back."},{"time":234820,"text":"He was hurt."},{"time":236715,"text":"He was trying to do something kind,"},{"time":238588,"text":"but Jonathan had rejected him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242113,"text":"I think we all reject people in small ways\nlike this without realizing it."},{"time":246288,"text":"I do."},{"time":247510,"text":"I'll walk by someone I know\nand barely acknowledge them."},{"time":250597,"text":"I'll check my phone\nwhen someone's talking to me."},{"time":253678,"text":"These acts devalue others."},{"time":255631,"text":"They make them feel\ninvisible and unworthy."},{"time":259130,"text":"But when you lead with love,\nyou create a bond"},{"time":261906,"text":"that lifts each of you up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":265030,"text":"For many people, belonging\nis the most essential source of meaning,"},{"time":268682,"text":"those bonds to family and friends."},{"time":271176,"text":"For others, the key to meaning\nis the second pillar: purpose."},{"time":275844,"text":"Now, finding your purpose\nis not the same thing"},{"time":278783,"text":"as finding that job that makes you happy."},{"time":281520,"text":"Purpose is less about what you want\nthan about what you give."},{"time":285003,"text":"A hospital custodian told me\nher purpose is healing sick people."},{"time":289515,"text":"Many parents tell me,"},{"time":291250,"text":"\"My purpose is raising my children.\""},{"time":293527,"text":"The key to purpose\nis using your strengths to serve others."},{"time":298381,"text":"Of course, for many of us,\nthat happens through work."},{"time":301913,"text":"That's how we contribute and feel needed."},{"time":304916,"text":"But that also means\nthat issues like disengagement at work,"},{"time":308800,"text":"unemployment,"},{"time":310237,"text":"low labor force participation --"},{"time":312488,"text":"these aren't just economic problems,\nthey're existential ones, too."},{"time":316821,"text":"Without something worthwhile to do,"},{"time":319058,"text":"people flounder."},{"time":321493,"text":"Of course, you don't have to find\npurpose at work,"},{"time":324133,"text":"but purpose gives you\nsomething to live for,"},{"time":326886,"text":"some \"why\" that drives you forward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":331147,"text":"The third pillar of meaning\nis also about stepping beyond yourself,"},{"time":334471,"text":"but in a completely different way:"},{"time":336337,"text":"transcendence."},{"time":337948,"text":"Transcendent states are those rare moments"},{"time":340349,"text":"when you're lifted above\nthe hustle and bustle of daily life,"},{"time":343785,"text":"your sense of self fades away,"},{"time":345514,"text":"and you feel connected\nto a higher reality."},{"time":349214,"text":"For one person I talked to,\ntranscendence came from seeing art."},{"time":352928,"text":"For another person, it was at church."},{"time":355482,"text":"For me, I'm a writer,\nand it happens through writing."},{"time":359060,"text":"Sometimes I get so in the zone\nthat I lose all sense of time and place."},{"time":364757,"text":"These transcendent\nexperiences can change you."},{"time":367927,"text":"One study had students look up\nat 200-feet-tall eucalyptus trees"},{"time":372475,"text":"for one minute."},{"time":374263,"text":"But afterwards\nthey felt less self-centered,"},{"time":376441,"text":"and they even behaved more generously"},{"time":378409,"text":"when given the chance to help someone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381582,"text":"Belonging, purpose, transcendence."},{"time":386374,"text":"Now, the fourth pillar\nof meaning, I've found,"},{"time":389121,"text":"tends to surprise people."},{"time":391366,"text":"The fourth pillar is storytelling,"},{"time":394124,"text":"the story you tell yourself\nabout yourself."},{"time":397616,"text":"Creating a narrative from the events\nof your life brings clarity."},{"time":401784,"text":"It helps you understand\nhow you became you."},{"time":405669,"text":"But we don't always realize\nthat we're the authors of our stories"},{"time":408789,"text":"and can change the way we're telling them."},{"time":410976,"text":"Your life isn't just a list of events."},{"time":413491,"text":"You can edit, interpret\nand retell your story,"},{"time":416731,"text":"even as you're constrained by the facts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419681,"text":"I met a young man named Emeka,\nwho'd been paralyzed playing football."},{"time":424920,"text":"After his injury, Emeka told himself,"},{"time":427403,"text":"\"My life was great playing football,"},{"time":430132,"text":"but now look at me.\""},{"time":434002,"text":"People who tell stories like this --"},{"time":436318,"text":"\"My life was good. Now it's bad.\" --"},{"time":438866,"text":"tend to be more anxious and depressed."},{"time":441712,"text":"And that was Emeka for a while."},{"time":444573,"text":"But with time, he started\nto weave a different story."},{"time":448415,"text":"His new story was,"},{"time":450172,"text":"\"Before my injury,\nmy life was purposeless."},{"time":453463,"text":"I partied a lot and was\na pretty selfish guy."},{"time":456740,"text":"But my injury made me realize\nI could be a better man.\""},{"time":461488,"text":"That edit to his story\nchanged Emeka's life."},{"time":465053,"text":"After telling the new story to himself,"},{"time":467508,"text":"Emeka started mentoring kids,"},{"time":469454,"text":"and he discovered what his purpose was:"},{"time":471844,"text":"serving others."},{"time":474101,"text":"The psychologist Dan McAdams\ncalls this a \"redemptive story,\""},{"time":477503,"text":"where the bad is redeemed by the good."},{"time":480627,"text":"People leading meaningful\nlives, he's found,"},{"time":482834,"text":"tend to tell stories about their lives"},{"time":484789,"text":"defined by redemption, growth and love."}]},{"cues":[{"time":488723,"text":"But what makes people\nchange their stories?"},{"time":491725,"text":"Some people get help from a therapist,"},{"time":493677,"text":"but you can do it on your own, too,"},{"time":495511,"text":"just by reflecting\non your life thoughtfully,"},{"time":498295,"text":"how your defining experiences shaped you,"},{"time":500406,"text":"what you lost, what you gained."},{"time":502589,"text":"That's what Emeka did."},{"time":505012,"text":"You won't change your story overnight;"},{"time":507082,"text":"it could take years and be painful."},{"time":509451,"text":"After all, we've all suffered,\nand we all struggle."},{"time":512957,"text":"But embracing those painful memories\ncan lead to new insights and wisdom,"},{"time":517320,"text":"to finding that good that sustains you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522584,"text":"Belonging, purpose,\ntranscendence, storytelling:"},{"time":527863,"text":"those are the four pillars of meaning."},{"time":531626,"text":"When I was younger,"},{"time":533256,"text":"I was lucky enough to be surrounded\nby all of the pillars."},{"time":537381,"text":"My parents ran a Sufi meetinghouse\nfrom our home in Montreal."},{"time":542686,"text":"Sufism is a spiritual practice\nassociated with the whirling dervishes"},{"time":547193,"text":"and the poet Rumi."},{"time":549430,"text":"Twice a week, Sufis would come to our home"},{"time":552029,"text":"to meditate, drink Persian tea,\nand share stories."},{"time":556209,"text":"Their practice also involved\nserving all of creation"},{"time":559190,"text":"through small acts of love,"},{"time":561024,"text":"which meant being kind\neven when people wronged you."},{"time":564389,"text":"But it gave them a purpose:\nto rein in the ego."}]},{"cues":[{"time":568912,"text":"Eventually, I left home for college"},{"time":571552,"text":"and without the daily grounding\nof Sufism in my life,"},{"time":575278,"text":"I felt unmoored."},{"time":576890,"text":"And I started searching for those things\nthat make life worth living."},{"time":580502,"text":"That's what set me on this journey."},{"time":583012,"text":"Looking back, I now realize"},{"time":584793,"text":"that the Sufi house\nhad a real culture of meaning."},{"time":588059,"text":"The pillars were part of the architecture,"},{"time":590589,"text":"and the presence of the pillars\nhelped us all live more deeply."}]},{"cues":[{"time":594414,"text":"Of course, the same principle applies"},{"time":596759,"text":"in other strong communities as well --"},{"time":598984,"text":"good ones and bad ones."},{"time":601556,"text":"Gangs, cults:"},{"time":603609,"text":"these are cultures of meaning\nthat use the pillars"},{"time":606646,"text":"and give people\nsomething to live and die for."},{"time":610048,"text":"But that's exactly why we as a society"},{"time":612939,"text":"must offer better alternatives."},{"time":615072,"text":"We need to build these pillars\nwithin our families and our institutions"},{"time":618847,"text":"to help people become their best selves."},{"time":622524,"text":"But living a meaningful life takes work."},{"time":625134,"text":"It's an ongoing process."},{"time":627033,"text":"As each day goes by,\nwe're constantly creating our lives,"},{"time":630786,"text":"adding to our story."},{"time":632831,"text":"And sometimes we can get off track."}]},{"cues":[{"time":636362,"text":"Whenever that happens to me,"},{"time":638297,"text":"I remember a powerful experience\nI had with my father."},{"time":643821,"text":"Several months after\nI graduated from college,"},{"time":646492,"text":"my dad had a massive heart attack\nthat should have killed him."},{"time":651033,"text":"He survived, and when I asked him\nwhat was going through his mind"},{"time":654271,"text":"as he faced death,"},{"time":655917,"text":"he said all he could think about\nwas needing to live"},{"time":658624,"text":"so he could be there\nfor my brother and me,"},{"time":660786,"text":"and this gave him the will\nto fight for life."},{"time":664063,"text":"When he went under anesthesia\nfor emergency surgery,"},{"time":667385,"text":"instead of counting backwards from 10,"},{"time":669739,"text":"he repeated our names like a mantra."},{"time":673790,"text":"He wanted our names to be\nthe last words he spoke on earth"},{"time":677625,"text":"if he died."}]},{"cues":[{"time":681033,"text":"My dad is a carpenter and a Sufi."},{"time":685185,"text":"It's a humble life,"},{"time":686756,"text":"but a good life."},{"time":688564,"text":"Lying there facing death,\nhe had a reason to live:"},{"time":692500,"text":"love."},{"time":693932,"text":"His sense of belonging within his family,"},{"time":696407,"text":"his purpose as a dad,"},{"time":698160,"text":"his transcendent meditation,\nrepeating our names --"},{"time":701198,"text":"these, he says, are the reasons\nwhy he survived."},{"time":704003,"text":"That's the story he tells himself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":707747,"text":"That's the power of meaning."},{"time":710643,"text":"Happiness comes and goes."},{"time":713459,"text":"But when life is really good"},{"time":715332,"text":"and when things are really bad,"},{"time":717241,"text":"having meaning gives you\nsomething to hold on to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720322,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721570,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}